<TEXT>
an earthquake measuring 68 on the richter scale 
rocked the tokyo area and southern japan early saturday but no 
damage or casualties were reported the central meteorological 
agency said 
the quake centered 310 miles south of tokyo in the pacific 
ocean struck at 843 am 743 pm edt friday 
there are no reports of damage or casualties a spokesman for 
the national police agency said saturday morning 
the meteorological agency said there was no danger of tidal waves 
along eastern japans pacific coast because the epicenter of the 
quake was too deep 
agency officials said the quakes epicenter was about 230 miles 
under the pacific 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph every increase of one number means that the ground 
motion is 10 times greater 
a quake of magnitude 6 can cause severe damage in populated 
areas while one measuring 7 is considered a major earthquake 
capable of widespread heavy damage 
</TEXT>
