<TEXT>
communist guerrillas said saturday 
that american servicemen in the philippines are targets for attacks 
the rebel new peoples army central luzon command made the 
warning in a statement released to news agencies 
also saturday a newspaper reported that guerrillas had trailed 
nine us servicemen apparently in preparation for an assassination 
attempt 
the rebels policy of punishing american troops deployed in 
us military installations in the country is still in force the 
guerrilla statement said it said about 1000 filipino soldiers 
providing additional security around clark air base also are targets 
the filipino troops were assigned to the us base last year 
following reports that guerrillas had trailed the nine us 
servicemen 
the pacific stars and stripes an unofficial us military 
newspaper quoted authorities as saying they learned of the 
surveillance through documents seized in july from the new peoples 
army 
the newspaper quoted police maj efren alamares as saying the 
nine two us air force colonels a lieutenant colonel four 
captains and two sergeants were apparently targeted because they 
lived off base 
the us military command at clark refused comment on the rebel 
statement capt donna eggelston a clark spokeswoman said the us 
air force periodically receives intelligence reports on terrorist 
activity but does not comment on their content 
communist guerrillas have attacked americans in the past 
in april guerrillas killed us army col james nick rowe as 
he drove to work at the joint us military assistance group in 
quezon city 
in october 1987 rebels killed three americans and a filipino 
civilian in coordinated ambushes outside clark 
the rebels have repeatedly threatened to attack us personnel 
because of washingtons support for president corazon aquinos 
campaign to crush the guerrillas 20year insurgency 
some 40000 american troops civilians and military dependents 
are stationed at six us military installations in the philippines 
more than half are stationed at clark in central luzon the main 
philippine island 
</TEXT>
