warrant emergency action or consumer concern 
alar spurs even growth in apples improves their appearance and 
gives them longer shelf life its use has dropped steadily in recent 
years as questions have been raised about its safety and after the 
most recent publicity its maker said it would be taken off the us 
market 
meanwhile the apple growers association is running an 
advertisement in papers sunday asking growers if they are interested 
in diverting all or part of their apples away from the marketplace 
as a way to raise wholesale prices to the breakeven point 
clements said the apples could be given to poor people churches 
or social service organizations rather than sold at a loss to 
retailers who clements contends are making large profits at the 
expense of growers 
growers accuse retailers of failing to cut supermarket prices in 
the wake of the plunging wholesale apple prices thus holding down 
consumer sales 
its flat crazy said grower rob valicoff saying that 
everyone but growers are making a profit off the crop 
retailers should be reducing their prices to sell more apples as 
a sign of support for the battered growers they contend 
the ad also asks growers if they are interested in pledging 
financial support to explore a lawsuit against those who helped 
trigger the alar controversy that would include the natural 
resources defense council which issued the disputed report and the 
cbs television program 60 minutes which gave the report what 
growers feel was unbalanced publicity 
the association which has 300 growermembers is asking for 
mailed responses to gauge the mood of the states 5000 growers and 
has not decided on any course of action clements said 
but the proposed actions are an indication of the desperation in 
this region that produces half the nations apples 
sales last week plunged to their lowest point of the year and 
prices sank further below the cost of production adding to the 
previous estimates of 100 million in losses for apple growers 
nationally as a result of the alar scare 
outofstate shipments fell to 843000 boxes 15 percent less 
than the week before and 32 percent less than for the same period 
last year according to the wenatchee valley traffic association 
wholesale prices dropped to 8 or less per 42pound box for the 
top grade of red delicious apples up to 4 less than last year and 
at least 2 below the cost of production according to market news 
service 
</TEXT>
