<TEXT>
time inc is asking shareholders to reject an 
unwanted 107 billion takeover bid from paramount communications 
corp and approve its decision to make an offer for its wouldbe 
merger partner warner communications inc 
in a letter to shareholders released saturday time reiterated 
the stand it took friday the media giant announced then it had 
turned down the paramount bid and amended the terms of its earlier 
stockswap merger agreement with warner to include a 14 billion 
