former president ronald reagan and singer stevie 
wonder joined hundreds of thousands of parisians saturday night in 
celebrating the 100th anniversary of the eiffel tower 
the crowd sang happy birthday at the end of an 89minute 
sound light and fireworks spectacle incorporating special 
effects 100 motorcycles and 5000 performers saluting the 
1000foot structure erected in 1889 
reagan was the guest of paris mayor jacques chirac whose city 
administration underwrote the 133 million cost of the production 
singers provided a range of styles from stevie wonder to 
placido domingo to french rocker johnny halliday and crooner charles 
trenet 
thousands of lights transformed the tower into a luminous 
spaceship one minute or a giant brooch of glittering multicolored 
jewels the next 
the spectacle was divided into three parts first evoking the 
french revolution of 1789 and the century leading up to the towers 
construction then the century from 1889 to today and finally the 
century of tomorrow 19892089 
giant screens relayed the show to an estimated 500000 people who 
gathered in the champs de mars under the tower on the seine bridges 
and at the trocadero across the river 
the towers birthday cake measured 65 feet across and 89 feet 
high 
a television special recording the celebration produced by radio 
city music hall productions is to be broadcast in france and at 
least 18 other countries 
