<TEXT>
a homemade gyrocopter crashed into a lake 
saturday killing two people authorities said 
the bodies of a kentucky couple were recovered from acton lake at 
hueston woods state park said park manager joel udstuen they were 
identified as robert w wahn 56 and his wife betty 48 both of 
verona 
mike stein of the ohio state patrol aviation division said 
gyrocopters differ from helicopters in that a helicopters engine 
drives the overhead rotor while a gyrocopters engine drives a rear 
rotor stein said backwash from the gyrocopters rear blade powers 
the overhead rotor 
pilots of gyrocopters must have a pilots license and register 
their aircraft with the federal aviation administration 
